Approved(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when the allowance of a spender is set by a token owner.

params.amount: The amount of tokens the spender is allowed to use.
params.owner: The address of the token owner setting the allowance.
params.spender: The address of the spender for whom the allowance is set.

Transfer(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when tokens are transferred from one address to another.

params.amount: The amount of tokens being transferred.
params.from: The address which is transferring tokens.
params.to: The address which is receiving the tokens.

allowance(address,address).details: Function to check the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.

params.owner: address The address which owns the funds.
params.spender: address The address which will spend the funds.

returns._0: A uint256 specifying the amount of tokens still available for the spender.

approve(address,uint256).details: Approve the passed address to spend the specified amount of tokens on behalf of msg.sender.

params.spender: The address which will spend the funds.
params.value: The amount of tokens to be spent.

balanceOf(address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address.

params.owner: The address to query the balance of.

returns._0: An uint256 representing the amount owned by the passed address.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Decrease the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.

params.spender: The address which will spend the funds.
params.subtractedValue: The amount of tokens to decrease the allowance by.

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Increase the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.

params.addedValue: The amount of tokens to increase the allowance by.
params.spender: The address which will spend the funds.

transfer(address,uint256).details: Transfer token for a specified address

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfer tokens from one address to another.

params.from: address The address which you want to send tokens from
params.to: address The address which you want to transfer to
params.value: uint256 the amount of tokens to be transferred

userdoc.notice: MyToken is an example contract that combines standard ERC20 capabilities          with the ability to pause and resume token transfers. It initializes with          a specified name, symbol, decimals, and total supply.

devdoc.details: Abstract contract providing an emergency stop mechanism, or "pause" feature.       Inherits from PauserRole to use role-based permissioning.

Paused(address).details: Emitted when the contract is paused.

params.account: The address of the account that triggered the pause.

PauserAdded(address).details: Emitted when a new pauser is added.

params.account: The address that is granted the pauser role.

PauserRemoved(address).details: Emitted when a pauser is removed.

params.account: The address that is removed from the pauser role.

Unpaused(address).details: Emitted when the contract is unpaused.

params.account: The address of the account that triggered the unpausing.

addPauser(address).details: Adds a new account to the pauser role. Can only be called by an existing pauser.

params.account: The address to be added to the pauser role.

constructor.details: Initializes the contract in an unpaused state.

isPauser(address).details: Checks if an account is a pauser.

params.account: The address to check.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the account has the pauser role.

pause().details: called by the owner to pause, triggers stopped state

returns._0: true if the contract is paused, false otherwise.

renouncePauser().details: Allows an account to renounce its role as a pauser.

unpause().details: called by the owner to unpause, returns to normal state

devdoc.title: Pausable

userdoc.notice: Allows derived contracts to implement pausable functionality, enabling authorized          accounts to pause and unpause contract operations in case of an emergency or other          significant events.

devdoc.details: Abstract contract for managing a pauser role, inheriting from the Roles library.       Provides the functionality to add and remove pausers.

PauserAdded(address).details: Emitted when a new pauser is added.

params.account: The address that is granted the pauser role.

PauserRemoved(address).details: Emitted when a pauser is removed.

params.account: The address that is removed from the pauser role.

addPauser(address).details: Adds a new account to the pauser role. Can only be called by an existing pauser.

params.account: The address to be added to the pauser role.

constructor.details: Initializes the contract by assigning the deployer as the initial pauser.

isPauser(address).details: Checks if an account is a pauser.

params.account: The address to check.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the account has the pauser role.

renouncePauser().details: Allows an account to renounce its role as a pauser.
